{"page_id": 54401, "slug": "End_of_Evangelion_Psalms", "title": "End of Evangelion Psalms", "display_title": "<span class=\"mw-page-title-main\">End of Evangelion Psalms</span>", "namespace": 0, "content_model": "wikitext", "language": null, "wikitext": "{{construction}}\n\n{{Publication\n| image       = [[Image:End_of_Evangelion_Psalms_Cover.jpg|200px]]\n| title          =End of Evangelion Psalms\n| alt_title       =The End of Evangelion: Boku to Iu Kigou\n| author       =Nobi Nobita\n| pub_date       =August 30, 1997\n| publisher         =Gentosha \n| pages        =141\n| dimensions        =16×16cm\n}}\n\n[[Image:End_of_Evangelion_Psalms_Example_Page.jpg|Example page. This compares [[Asuka]] and [[Shinji|Shinji's]] choking scene to their kiss scene from [[Episode 15]], by reinserting their dialogue in there.|thumb|left|250px]]\n\n'''End of Evangelion Psalms''' is a 1997 book by Gainax apparently. It is a collection of select dialogue from the select episodes of the series with some minor commentary inserted.\n\nIn keeping with Eva's usage of religious symbolism, a ''psalm'' can be referred to as:\n\n''1. (religion, music) A sacred song; a poetical composition for use in the praise or worship of God.''\n\n''2. One of the hymns by David and others, collected into one book of the Old Testament, or a modern metrical version of such a hymn for public worship.''<ref>[https://en.wiktionary.org/wiki/psalm Wiktionary]</ref>\n\nThis book is apparently by doujin artist Nobi Nobita<ref>https://forum.evageeks.org/post/425333/NGE-Ep24-Script-First-and-Second-Drafts/#425333</ref>, author of Bridal Veil.<ref>https://forum.evageeks.org/thread/17938/Nobi-Nobita-Bridal-Veil-Ep-22-DC-Source</ref>\n<br><br><br><br><br><br><br><br><br>\n==Notes==\n\n{{reflist}}\n\n{{Pub List}}\n\n[[Category:A to Z]]\n[[Category:Publications]]\n\n{{stub}}", "html": "<div class=\"mw-parser-output\"><table align=\"center\" style=\"border:2px solid Gold; width:85%; background:LemonChiffon;\">\n\n<tbody><tr>\n<td><span typeof=\"mw:File\"><a href=\"/File:Eva2-22_C0306_comp.jpg\" class=\"mw-file-description\"><img src=\"/images/thumb/3/33/Eva2-22_C0306_comp.jpg/180px-Eva2-22_C0306_comp.jpg\" decoding=\"async\" width=\"180\" height=\"104\" class=\"mw-file-element\" srcset=\"/images/thumb/3/33/Eva2-22_C0306_comp.jpg/270px-Eva2-22_C0306_comp.jpg 1.5x, /images/thumb/3/33/Eva2-22_C0306_comp.jpg/360px-Eva2-22_C0306_comp.jpg 2x\" /></a></span>\n</td>\n<td style=\"text-align:center;\">\n<p><big><b>\"<i>We've seen it. The proof of its construction was very useful.</i>\"</b></big><br />\nThis article or section is <b>under construction</b>, and needs to be further expanded.<br />\n<small>Please provide input on the talk page, or  help build this page.</small>\n</p>\n</td></tr></tbody></table>\n<table class=\"infobox\" style=\"width: 200; text-align: left; font-size: 100%;\" cellspacing=\"2\">\n\n<tbody><tr>\n<td colspan=\"2\" align=\"center\" width=\"150px\"><span typeof=\"mw:File\"><a href=\"/File:End_of_Evangelion_Psalms_Cover.jpg\" class=\"mw-file-description\"><img src=\"/images/thumb/c/ce/End_of_Evangelion_Psalms_Cover.jpg/200px-End_of_Evangelion_Psalms_Cover.jpg\" decoding=\"async\" width=\"200\" height=\"206\" class=\"mw-file-element\" srcset=\"/images/thumb/c/ce/End_of_Evangelion_Psalms_Cover.jpg/300px-End_of_Evangelion_Psalms_Cover.jpg 1.5x, /images/thumb/c/ce/End_of_Evangelion_Psalms_Cover.jpg/400px-End_of_Evangelion_Psalms_Cover.jpg 2x\" /></a></span>\n</td></tr>\n<tr>\n<th width=\"200px\">Title\n</th>\n<td>End of Evangelion Psalms\n</td></tr>\n<tr>\n<th>\n</th>\n<td>The End of Evangelion: Boku to Iu Kigou\n</td></tr>\n\n<tr>\n<th>Author\n</th>\n<td>Nobi Nobita\n</td></tr>\n<tr>\n<th>Original Publication Date\n</th>\n<td>August 30, 1997\n</td></tr>\n<tr>\n<th>Publisher\n</th>\n<td>Gentosha\n</td></tr>\n<tr>\n<th>Pages\n</th>\n<td>141\n</td></tr>\n\n<tr>\n<th>Dimensions\n</th>\n<td>16×16cm\n</td></tr>\n\n\n</tbody></table>\n<figure class=\"mw-halign-left\" typeof=\"mw:File/Thumb\"><a href=\"/File:End_of_Evangelion_Psalms_Example_Page.jpg\" class=\"mw-file-description\"><img src=\"/images/thumb/1/1e/End_of_Evangelion_Psalms_Example_Page.jpg/250px-End_of_Evangelion_Psalms_Example_Page.jpg\" decoding=\"async\" width=\"250\" height=\"265\" class=\"mw-file-element\" srcset=\"/images/thumb/1/1e/End_of_Evangelion_Psalms_Example_Page.jpg/375px-End_of_Evangelion_Psalms_Example_Page.jpg 1.5x, /images/thumb/1/1e/End_of_Evangelion_Psalms_Example_Page.jpg/500px-End_of_Evangelion_Psalms_Example_Page.jpg 2x\" /></a><figcaption>Example page. This compares <a href=\"/Asuka\" class=\"mw-redirect\" title=\"Asuka\">Asuka</a> and <a href=\"/Shinji\" class=\"mw-redirect\" title=\"Shinji\">Shinji's</a> choking scene to their kiss scene from <a href=\"/Episode_15\" title=\"Episode 15\">Episode 15</a>, by reinserting their dialogue in there.</figcaption></figure>\n<p><b>End of Evangelion Psalms</b> is a 1997 book by Gainax apparently. It is a collection of select dialogue from the select episodes of the series with some minor commentary inserted.\n</p><p>In keeping with Eva's usage of religious symbolism, a <i>psalm</i> can be referred to as:\n</p><p><i>1. (religion, music) A sacred song; a poetical composition for use in the praise or worship of God.</i>\n</p><p><i>2. One of the hymns by David and others, collected into one book of the Old Testament, or a modern metrical version of such a hymn for public worship.</i><sup id=\"cite_ref-1\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-1\">&#91;1&#93;</a></sup>\n</p><p>This book is apparently by doujin artist Nobi Nobita<sup id=\"cite_ref-2\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-2\">&#91;2&#93;</a></sup>, author of Bridal Veil.<sup id=\"cite_ref-3\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-3\">&#91;3&#93;</a></sup>\n<br /><br /><br /><br /><br /><br /><br /><br /><br />\n</p>\n<h2><span class=\"mw-headline\" id=\"Notes\">Notes</span><span class=\"mw-editsection\"><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">[</sp